## Quality gate

This project carries the shared quality baseline: prek hooks (git hygiene, gitleaks,
typos, rumdl, SPDX/REUSE headers{% if has_python %}, ruff, ty{% endif %}) that run
identically locally and in CI. Conventional Commits are enforced at commit-msg time
(`.cz.toml`); releases on `main` are managed by release-please (a Release PR →
`vX.Y.Z` tag + GitHub Release on merge).

```bash
uvx prek run --all-files   # run every hook on demand
```

A few hooks shell out to **system tools** prek can't bootstrap — CI installs them for
you, but install them locally too (most are in Homebrew): `hawkeye`, `taplo`{% if include_terraform or include_docker %}, `trivy`{% endif %}{% if has_python %}, `osv-scanner`{% endif %}{% if include_terraform %}, `terraform`, `tflint`{% endif %}{% if include_helm %}, `helm`{% endif %}.
